The paper deals with knowledge graph completion, which is a task related to artificial intelligence and machine learning (cs.AI). The proposed method involves modeling relational context and paths, which are common techniques in graph-based machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also uses knowledge graphs as its main data source, which is a topic related to databases (cs.DB). The method involves message passing, which is a common technique in natural language processing (cs.CL) and graph-based machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with the task of predicting missing relations, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR).
